INSERT INTO public.vacancy (id, about, broker, company, hours, posting_date, salary, title, vacancy_number, vacancyurl, location_id) VALUES ('7030243f-b5df-42c3-bc7a-1cdbdb1a32d9', '<p>As the owner of the position Center of Competence (CoC) Miles and Mobility, you will drive the end-to-end responsibility for providing regional solutions for contract management &amp; accounting and global telematics/mobility propositions. Your team will be instrumental to enable our demanding business units by delivering business value continuously by the Scrum teams as well as ensuring second and third-level support for the IT services provided. </p>
<p>The contract management &amp; accounting solutions are used in 5-6 markets, the telematics and mobility solutions are provided globally, managed by a virtual team of more than 10 people. As part of an agile IT leadership team, you will also help explore new working models and solutions to boost our digital transformation.</p>
<ul>
 <li>Oversee and direct the day-to-day IT development and ensure that systems, services, and infrastructure work reliably and securely across all locations,</li>
 <li>Foster standardization of the solutions by developing a common standard for contract management &amp; accounting systems,&nbsp;</li>
 <li>Establish and maintain an integrated demand &amp; release management process to deliver business value and stable operations of the services towards your customers,</li>
 <li>Ensure optimization and maintenance of services and the development of processes (incident, problem, release, configuration, change),</li>
 <li>Plan, structure, organize and develop the assigned team members, IT suppliers and processes, in such a way that the team become #TwiceAsFast,</li>
 <li>Align solutions designs of projects with Enterprise Architecture and the other IT governance roles,&nbsp;</li>
 <li>Support the further development of an integrated IT system template (Blueprint) for the countries,</li>
 <li>Own and stay within your cost center in the operational budget for your area of responsibility,</li>
 <li>Maintain and build trusted relationships with all business units and other country-specific departments,</li>
 <li>Establish new cooperation models with countries and/or internal managed service providers to constantly increase the efficiency of IT delivery,</li>
 <li>Ensure full compliance with Daimler AG policies and local legislation,</li>
 <li>Team objectives and key results are defined, discussed, and completed on a quarterly base,</li>
 <li>Make Product Owners successful by providing strategic input and guidance,</li>
 <li>Individual development plans for each of your team members are in place and fulfilled,</li>
 <li>Cultivate an inclusive, positive, and respectful working environment within IT.&nbsp;</li>
</ul> Functie-eisen
<p>You have a record of accomplishment in managing and developing high performing teams. You have strong communication and stakeholder management skills. Good knowledge of operational fleet &amp; leasing business and in the context of intercultural cooperation in the accounting area. A proven record in a similar international position and strong experience in managing international projects.&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
 <li>Bachelors’ Degree in preferably computer science, management information systems or a related technical field,</li>
 <li>12+ years of relevant professional experience with progressively increasing responsibility in agile software development projects and a minimum of 5+ years managing IT service delivery teams,</li>
 <li>Strong knowledge in agile frameworks like e.g. SCRUM, Kanban and the respective tools e.g. Jira, Confluence,</li>
 <li>Additional language skills next to English are beneficial,</li>
 <li>You are willing and able to travel approx. once a month.</li>
</ul> Competenties
<ul>
 <li>Integrity, Openness and Respect,</li>
 <li>Inspired, Empowered and Diverse People,</li>
 <li>Customer Focus,</li>
 <li>Commitment to Excellence,</li>
 <li>Financial &amp; Social Responsibility.</li>
</ul> Arbeidsvoorwaarden
<p>We offer an open-minded organization with a professionally challenging and informal working environment, where you can reach your full potential. We believe your talent can add great value to our skills. In return, we offer you the opportunity to build an international career within our global mobility provider.</p>
<p>If you join us, we will offer you:</p>
<ul>
 <li>Depending on experience, a competitive year salary based on 38-hour workweek, including 13th month and holiday allowance)</li>
 <li>Company pension scheme (Employer pays the full contribution of this pension)</li>
 <li>Employee Budget (EB), to be used for commuting costs, extra hours of leave, and other things</li>
 <li>Extensive Mobility Policy, for which you can use your Employee Budget (EB)</li>
 <li>Variable bonus based on the company''s results and personal performance targets</li>
 <li>26 days of leave (based on 38-hour workweek)</li>
 <li>Laptop / Smartphone / Lease car</li>
 <li>Flexible working hours with the possibility to work from home (where possible in the scope of your responsibilities)</li>
</ul>
<p>Employee involvement is important, therefore you can spend two working days annually volunteering for a local charity.</p>
