<p>Are you an experienced Cyber security engineer with a passion for automation and complex challenges? We are looking for you to join our growing Cyber Engineering team.<br><br>ASML brings together the most creative minds in science and technology to develop lithography machines that are key to producing faster, cheaper, more energy-efficient microchips. We design, develop, integrate, market and service these advanced machines, which enable our customers - the world''s leading chipmakers - to reduce the size and increase the functionality of their microchips, which in turn leads to smaller, more powerful consumer electronics.<br>The Cyber Defense Center (CDC) within ASML (Veldhoven office) through real time detection &amp; response minimizes the damage caused by threat actors bypassing ASML preventative security controls and protecting ASML information.<br>To enhance our Cyber resilience, the Cyber engineering team continuously develops and onboards new detection and response capabilities on a global scale.<br>Our team works closely together with other security functions and other ASML teams utilizing our shared in depth knowledge in this effort to secure the business for all our stakeholders.<br><br><b>Job Mission</b></p>
<p>You participate in developing and onboarding new detection &amp; response capabilities in order to keep up with the developing threat landscape.<br><br><b>Job Description</b>Execute solution engineering and technical architecture; integrate security technologies<br>Create and optimize workflows<br>Onboarding of new logfiles and use cases<br>Onboarding of new technical and functional service components within the portfolio of the CDC<br>Automation of detection and response capabilities<br>Collaborate with colleagues in the other value streams of the CDC as other technology departments to establish effective and productive relationships.</p>  Over de werkgever
<p>ASML is a world leader in the manufacture of advanced technology systems for the semiconductor industry. The company offers an integrated portfolio for manufacturing complex integrated circuits (also called ICs or chips). ASML designs, develops, integrates, markets and services advanced systems used by customers - the major global semiconductor manufacturers - to create chips that power a wide array of electronic, communications and information technology products.</p>  Vaardigheden  EducationBachelor or Master''s degree in cyber security, Computer science or equivalent combination of education and work experienceExperience5-10 years of experience working in an agile Cyber Engineering team within an enterprise environment;Minimum of 2 years of experience working in an analyst/incident responder role within an enterprise environment;Hands-on experience working in cloud environmentsExperience with CI/CD pipeline and/or the cloud-based tools that support themPersonal skillsCritical thinking and contextual analysis abilities;Investigative and analytical problem solving skills;Teamwork, can-do mentality;Stress resistant and natural multi-tasker;Result driven;Good documentation skills;Strong time management skills and willing to go above and beyond where required.Context of the positionKnowledge ofExperience with Object oriented development, and at least one scripting/ programming e.g. Python, C, Java, PowerShell;Experience with automation/configuration management toolingHand-on experience developing solution with SIEM tools (e.g. Splunk)Hand-on experience planning, designing, creating, debugging automation playbooks with SOAR platforms;Strong experience in security solutions and agile design principles/practices, DevOps methodologies/tools and SDLC;Operating systems, including Windows and Linux;Networking concepts, including TCP/IP protocols and network topology;Data lake concepts;Proficient in English (business language);Ability to work collaboratively across a variety of business unit or value streams to implement automation and orchestrationExperience with security analytics, and / or threat hunting is a pre.Willing to work outside office hours due to the global presence of the teamThe certifications below are a pre;GCIA, GPYC, CEPP, Splunk certified developer
