INSERT INTO public.vacancy (id, about, broker, company, hours, posting_date, salary, title, vacancy_number, vacancyurl, location_id) VALUES ('0cea4925-a83f-4342-aac0-695cdf211d75', '<p><b>Chapter Lead Platform Engineering – Consumer Loans</b></p>
<p><br>Do you love tech and are you an ambassador for the agile way of working? Want to work in an multidisciplinary team, and bring out the best in people?</p>
<p>We’re looking for an energetic IT chapter lead who combines thought and action. Are you an explorer and knowledgeable about what IT can do? Then jump on into our global IT community</p>
<p><b>We’re on a mission</b></p>
<p>We’re building the ING of tomorrow. More and more people live their lives on digital platforms. And although competition is fierce, this is where we want to be. We want to be part of people’s lives, helping them make better decisions. Become the go-to-place for their financial matters. What will our digital future look like? We’re building it right now. And that’s where you come in.</p>
<p>Do you take your own development and those of others serious, have a ‘no nonsense’ and ‘getting-things-done’ mentality and deserved your kudos as a well-respected engineer, then you might be the IT Chapter Lead Platform Engineering we are looking for.</p>
<p><b>About Consumer Loans</b><br>ING Consumer Loans is a cross border organization that serves the Dutch and the Belgian market. The main focus for the upcoming period is on digitalization of our product and processes to improve the customer experience.</p>
<p>The majority of the development is done on our Pega platform which is hosted by the One Pega Platform team. Next this our technology stack consists of virtualized Linux environments and technologies likes TC-server with Lit-HTML/Web Components/ Polymer/ Angular JS in combination with rest API’s (Java based on Spring framework) and Oracle/Cassandra.</p>
<p><b>Your role</b></p>
<p>As an IT Chapter Lead you are a seasoned senior engineer and you are seen by colleagues as a go-to person. You will become a Chapter Lead within the IT Area Mortgages NL and Consumer Loans. Along with the IT Area Lead and your fellow IT Chapter Leads you set the standards for software development and operations in your area of expertise. You have not only a strong drive to constantly keep your own expertise up to speed, but also want to make an active contribution to the development and advancement of the people in your chapter and your field.</p>
<p>As an IT Chapter Lead, you are a “doer”. Sixty percent of your time, you work as a senior engineer in a squad. You use your expertise to maximize team performance. You will work with cutting-edge technology while you’re pushing innovation in an environment where you have the possibility to show your work on a platform with huge user bases/high traffic: the applications you work on are used by millions of customers on a daily basis. The people in your chapter are equally ambitious as you, and you like to transfer your expertise to them and feel satisfaction from coaching (both professionally as personally) your chapter members. You also encourage and facilitate the sharing of content and experience amongst them. They work in an international environment in different multidisciplinary squads, together with business colleagues, UX designers, visuals designers product owners.</p>
<p><b>What do we expect from you?</b></p>
<ul>
 <li><p>Team lead experience with a proven ability to bring out the best in people and drive the team forward</p></li>
 <li><p>You know what it takes to run large scale environments with 24x7 availability</p></li>
 <li><p>Native Dutch, both written and oral are a must for this role</p></li>
 <li><p>Automation of the engineering activities has no secrets for you; e.g. Continuous Integration and Deployment pipelines, Automated testing</p></li>
 <li><p>Able to build a network with supporting departments to ensure smooth execution of new installations, stability and monitoring of the environments</p></li>
 <li><p>Management of life cycle management activities</p></li>
 <li><p>An eye for problems and structural solution of incidents</p></li>
 <li><p>Make sure that all environments are up to standards with regard to our security guidelines</p></li>
 <li><p>Have a strong interest and vision in recent trends in software development, operations and technology in general.</p></li>
 <li><p>Great analytical skills and conceptual / architectural understanding, ability to learn new technical concepts fast.</p></li>
 <li><p>You embrace change and you are not afraid of frequently changing project direction or stakeholder environment.</p></li>
 <li><p>Ability to constantly balance the pressure of commercial targets of the teams you oversee and the quality of software they deliver to production</p></li>
 <li><p>Experienced in Agile / Scrum / DevOps methodologies</p></li>
 <li><p>Last but not least, hard-working, down-to-earth mentality. When a feature is broken with customer impact, you and your team will fix it: here and now.</p></li>
</ul>
<p><b>What you’ll get in return</b></p>
<ul>
 <li><p>The chance to work in a global, innovation-driven company that loves tech.</p></li>
 <li><p>An international and diverse network of engineering experts.</p></li>
 <li><p>Full support for your personal growth and professional development through excellent courses and programs.</p></li>
 <li><p>An agile, vibrant and flexible work environment.</p></li>
 <li><p>Great work-life balance.</p></li>
 <li><p>A competitive salary and excellent benefits, like a 13th month, pension scheme, personal allowance, laptop, mobile phone.</p></li>
</ul>
<p><b>Questions?</b><br>Contact the recruiter attached to the advertisement for more information. Want to apply directly? Please upload your CV and motivation letter by clicking the “Apply” button.</p>
<p><b>About us</b></p>
<p>With around 52,000 employees and operations in approximately 40 countries, there is no shortage of opportunities for people with initiative who want to make a difference. We hire smart people like you for your potential, not your past. Our biggest expectation is that you’ll stay curious. Keep learning. Take on more responsibility. In return, we’ll back you to develop into an even more awesome version of yourself. If you want to work at the cutting edge of what’s possible, surrounded by progressive, inspiring and supportive colleagues, there is no better place to invest your talents than at ING.</p>   <strong>Type vacature:</strong>  Intern   Vaardigheden
