INSERT INTO public.vacancy (id, about, broker, company, hours, posting_date, salary, title, vacancy_number, vacancyurl, location_id) VALUES ('6dfcf532-0e26-468c-b46b-cc82c4e2df41', '<p>We are looking for an engineer who can get used to working with a vendor provided platform, since we are using Apache Kafka based Axual Platform as a SAAS solution. Both development and operations experience are important.</p>
<p>You are working for the Integration department and are responsible for managing millions of Apache Kafka events and messaging calls per day. You, as Medior Cloud Integration DevOps Engineer (Eventing &amp; Messaging), help other DevOps teams within the Rabobank to build, manage and consume their own events using a self-service Apache Kafka portal. Next step is that we want to expand our scope to Enterprise level and assist the International&nbsp;too.<br><br>We are looking for an engineer who can get used to working with a vendor provided platform, since we are using Apache Kafka based Axual Platform as a SAAS solution. Both development and operations experience are important.</p>
<p>From the development side we have an interest in mainly Java and GIT experience, but also Python, Maven and BASH Scripting are used. Experience with Apache Camel in combination with Apache Kafka or Kafka Connect is plus.</p>
<p>From the operations side we are using Docker, Kubernetes on the Rancher platform, Azure DevOps and PCF, Linux scripting and general Linux knowledge. We are currently planning a CI/CD pipeline for team related artefacts which is going to run on Azure DevOps. In this area we appreciate experience with Azure DevOps, Jenkins, GIT and build pipelines.<br><br>Next to being a developer and operations engineer, we advise and help our customers who are building event streaming applications based on Apache Kafka. So regular customer contact is part of the job. This will be done via Person of the Day shifts and via consulting sessions with teams who are onboarding to our offering. Because our internal customers are starting with event streaming with Apache Kafka, we appreciate all experience with the following; Apache Spark, Apache Cassandra, Apache Camel, Flink, Storm, Elastic Search, Kibana and of course Apache Kafka are all relevant in this space.<br>Our department is in a transition towards a DevOps way of working in which our Integration engineers are T-shaped across multiple Cloud platforms. Part of the current transition is that we will shift towards a more customer oriented service model that relies heavily on automation. As Integration Area we want to support other Rabobank DevOps teams to Do it Yourself (DiY). This means that rather than doing it for them, we enable them to manage, provide and consume their cloud solutions within one of our Cloud platforms. Increasing their autonomy and therefore realizing a faster time to market. This means that next to being their contact point with in depth knowledge, you will be seeking ways to automate their requests and "How to?" questions via our centralised IntegrationDesk and IntegrationHub. You have a great understanding of Cloud market trends and are excited to include this on your teams Backlog as a surprising feature for our business.<br><br>You will help other DevOps teams throughout our client&nbsp;adapt and embrace Event streaming with Apache Kafka. You will be seen as an eventing evangelist and are going to help feature teams to get an understanding of Eventing using Apache Kafka. Next to that you will maintain and contribute to a growing catalogue of excellent Eventing patterns using Apache Kafka. Our team will start to maintain several MQ bridges in the near future. These bridges transfer millions of events to Apache Kafka per day.<br>Rabobank is the first company in the Netherlands which has adapted Apache Kafka through the Axual Platform. With the Axual Platform our internal customers themselves can create producers, consumers or streaming apps with ease, to exchange any type of data.<br><br>Make a difference<br>• You actively support other DevOps teams on Do it Yourself solutions (Event Streaming) by advising them on individual or group basis and by providing trainings and demo''s.<br>• With help of your team you automate your own recurring work e.g. through Ansible, Git, Jenkins, Python or Java (combining this with the IntegrationDesk and IntegrationHub).<br>• You generate and maintain your team specific content at the new created IntegrationHub.<br>• You develop features for our consumers (other DevOps teams) and assist in building our own Azure DevOps pipelines for the on premise infra.<br>• You proactively help your team grow in their own Agile way of working and team autonomy. You do so by addressing improvements and providing feedback so we continuously GROW.<br>• You are communicative and are able to tell our consumers why traditional solutions should be moving to the Cloud.<br>• You are calm and patient by nature and are willing to contribute to a transition from traditional messaging to either Event Streaming or align with your colleagues from the API team. This transition will take several years.<br>With each other<br>• We need to be innovative and embrace the movement towards the public Cloud.<br>• We encourage out of the box thinking to come up with the best solutions.<br>• We GROW by challenging and helping each other as well by providing feedback.<br>• We serve a broad scale of activities requiring you to be flexible and open minded.</p>  Over de werkgever
<p>Our client''s Wholesale &amp; Rural (W&amp;R) is the Client''s Group wholesale and investment banking operation and has established a world-class reputation in the Food &amp; Agri sector. Rabobank W&amp;R serves clients which are among the leading multinational Corporates and renowned financial institutions and are served through 140 offices in 42 countries. The employees are at the heart of the success of W&amp;R.<br><br>The Systems team is responsible within Our client''s W&amp;R for the development, maintenance and support of all IT applications and interfaces worldwide. The Finance &amp; Accounting team is responsible within Systems for all projects and management of IT applications for Finance, with the objective of delivering timely and correct financial data in order to meet dynamic and challenging regulatory and internal demands.</p>
<p>Do you want this too?<br>Be the best version of yourself? We are happy to help you by focussing your development and investing in an environment in which you continue to learn. We give you the space to innovate and undertake. For example, we offer you plenty of growth opportunities and help you surpass your expectations and do the right things exceptionally well, so that you can grow as a professional. </p>
<ul>
 <li>On top of that you can also count on us (based on a 36-hour working week):</li>
 <li>A thirteenth month and holiday money;</li>
 <li>An Employee Benefit Budget (10% of your monthly income). How you bet this budget is up to you. Consider buying extra holiday days or an additional deposit in your pension;</li>
 <li>Relatively high flexibility in working hours and location independent work, depending on the planning in the team;</li>
 <li>100% reimbursement of commuting if you travel with ov! Anyway with car or motorbike? </li>
</ul>
<p>Then choose a commuting fee;</p>
<ul>
 <li>A pension scheme that you only contribute 5% to.</li>
</ul>Let''s get acquainted.&nbsp;
<br>Are you him/her? The new colleague who wants to strengthen our clientas a Red Team Operator and to make the difference for yourself, our customers and society?&nbsp; We would like to receive your application on this vacancy in Utrecht.
<br>&nbsp;
<br>Useful to know:
<br>&nbsp;
<br>Even if you do not meet the profile of 100%, but you think the role can be perfectly fulfilled, we ask you to apply, we invest in your growth and development.
<br>Responses are handled in accordance with vacancy management.
<br>Felix de Bruin IT Recruiter is happy to answer questions about the application process via mail or applying to the according link.
<br>Screening is part of the application process. We test on the basis of the screening procedures that apply within our client or if new employees are sufficiently reliable to carry out work at our client.
<br>For this vacancy, an individual assessment and a test of your skills can be part of the application process.
<br>Everyone is different, and precisely the differences in people help us to be an even better bank. That''s why we are curious about who you.
<p></p>  Vaardigheden  We consider part of the DevOps T-shape; analyst/consultancy, programming, operations, security, testing, infrastructure and CI/CD. For you as Medior Cloud Integration DevOps Engineer T-shaped means that you have a competent understanding of Integration and middleware. You have sufficient in depth expertise in three of these and a broader/basic knowledge on at least three other aspects.• At least five years experience in software development and systems administration• Experience with the eventing technologies like Apache Kafka, Zookeeper, Flink, Spark, Cassandra• Experience in the messages technologies like IBM Websphere, WebLogic• You have experience with Docker and Kubernetes• You have experience working with Apache Kafka• You can explain to other engineers how Event Streaming works with Apache Kafka• A Bachelor or Master degree in preferably an Engineering degree• Three of the following:o Cloud Engineer on Azure and/or AWS.o Automation skills and/or active configuration knowledge like Ansible and Git.o You are experienced in building CI/CD pipelines for software development.o You have knowledge and experience with test automation (including unit test).o Knowledge of Linux and operations experience with Apache Kafka / Zookeeper.o You have implemented new technologies and dare to be one of our first employees to experiment with new technologies such as Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, chatbots, Internet of Things.• You have understanding of Agile and are willing to certify yourself as DevOps Engineer.Due to Rabobank interest in support a diverse work environment, when profiles are comparable, we like to show interest for a female Engineer.
