INSERT INTO public.vacancy (id, about, broker, company, hours, posting_date, salary, title, vacancy_number, vacancyurl, location_id) VALUES ('ee44ffbd-c247-4a6a-a944-0280e9f5f5da', 'Java developer Job description
<p><strong>Amsterdam</strong><em> - </em>As a Java developer within our Selectives Area you will contribute to making sure our millions of readers get the highest quality features. </p>
<p><br></p>
<p>On a daily basis, our content impacts millions of readers, making DPG Media the biggest media house of The Netherlands and Belgium. We have built a white-label platform for web and app, desktop, mobile and tablet use. This platform services our premium news brands: De Volkskrant, Trouw, Het Parool, De Morgen and HUMO.<br></p>
<p><strong><br></strong></p>
<p><strong>What you will be doing</strong></p>
<p>Because you’re working in a huge landscape with advanced technologies, you will keep on learning every day. You will build backend applications/features in the cloud while always striving for the best code quality and applying security measures. Your main tasks are:</p>
<ul>
 <li>“You build it, you run it”: designing, coding, testing, deploying, implementing new components and doing day-to-day operations of all our backend components.</li>
 <li>Identifying bottlenecks and improving the system to make it more robust, scalable and work fluently.</li>
 <li>Sharing knowledge with our other backend developers and together making sure our platform grows and moves in the right direction.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><br></strong></p>
<p>Our stack:<strong></strong><strong>Java 8/11, REST, Spring Boot, Maven/Gradle, AWS Services, Hibernate and Docker.</strong></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong>About the team</strong></p>
<p>The team you’ll be working in, is responsible for creating and maintaining features that our readers will be using. This is a cross functional, devops team so you will be the backend developer for the team working with frontend, app developers and QA engineers. With your team members you will work together closely, have a lot of contact and keep on improving.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p><em>“We want to offer the highest quality to our readers, we give our best every day and make sure we create the backend to keep on moving and improving”</em></p>
<p><strong><br></strong></p>
<p><strong>We offer</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>An experience-based salary.</li>
 <li>36-hour workweek.</li>
 <li>12% in flexible benefits (of which 8% is holiday allowance).</li>
 <li>A percentage of profit shares.</li>
 <li>Reimbursement of travel expenses.</li>
 <li>24 paid holiday days.</li>
 <li>Location in Amsterdam.</li>
 <li>Fully paid functional technical training.</li>
</ul> Job requirements
<p><strong>Who are you</strong></p>
<p>You love learning new things and keep a close eye on technological evolutions. You are open-minded and critical with a no-nonsense approach: always looking for the ‘why’ of things. Also, you are passionate about IT and development, always focused on quality. What else we expect:</p>
<ul>
 <li>At least 6 years of professional experience with Java 8, Spring and Amazon Web Services. Experience with Java 11 is a great advantage. You should be familiar with CI/CD, Security and REST.</li>
 <li>You to have a team-oriented Agile mindset and experience with Scrum and DevOps.</li>
 <li>You to speak English fluently and preferably Dutch on a professional level.</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong>Are you going to be our new colleague? Apply now!</strong></p>
<p>Do you still have some more questions? I will happily answer those via mark.van.dommelen@dpgmedia.nl +316 83 80 00 59. A WhatsApp message is also possible.</p>
