INSERT INTO public.vacancy (id, about, broker, company, hours, posting_date, salary, title, vacancy_number, vacancyurl, location_id) VALUES ('c91cc348-d96a-4dbf-af2b-e9b64e327380', '<p>For our Payments Channels department within ING Wholesale Bank, we’re looking for a Full-stack Developer to strengthen its teams.</p>
<p>If you want to work at a place where you and your colleagues are working with the newest stacks and technologies, where investing in the automation of provisioning and monitoring never stops, and where we are building a team of top-notch Dev Engineers that can take on the challenges of developing the most important internet-facing applications of one of the largest Global Banks, please read on.</p>
<p><b>What you’ll do</b></p>
<ul>
 <li><p>You will be part of a squad: a self-managing, autonomous unit with end-to-end responsibility for a customer journey, e.g. the online payments by big corporates, our Wholesale clients. </p></li>
 <li><p>You will be involved in the whole development lifecycle, from refining user stories until monitoring software in production, where your main focus will be coding.</p></li>
 <li><p>You build, enhance and maintain our APIs with an internal Spring (Boot) based framework and run on virtualized hardware.</p></li>
 <li><p>You develop screens using the internal Web Components stack built with lit-html and LitElement.</p></li>
 <li><p>You apply continuous delivery practices as part of our daily work.</p></li>
 <li><p>You implement mandatory security standards to ensure IT risk is and remain under control.</p></li>
</ul>
<p><b>Your personality</b></p>
<ul>
 <li><p>You are open, you contribute to the development of your squad by giving and accepting direct feedback</p></li>
 <li><p>You have a focus on quality and challenge your colleagues (e.g. during peer reviews)</p></li>
 <li><p>You speak up and challenge decisions, you ask why things are done instead of just doing them</p></li>
 <li><p>You continuously develop your own expertise while gathering, updating and spreading knowledge about developments and challenges regarding your field and embed lessons learned and best practices</p></li>
 <li><p>You’re eager to step out from your comfort zone. Where possible, you take on tasks/activities that contribute to the purpose even when they are not entirely within your area of expertise</p></li>
</ul>
<p><b>Your skills</b></p>
